        "content": "<p>I am looking for a lemma that states that if <code>C</code> is an empty category (<code>C ≃ Empty</code>) , and a functor <code>F : C ⥤ D</code> has a limit, then the limit is the terminal object of <code>D</code>. I've searched for it on the Mathlib doc, and on moogle, but couldn't find it.</p>",
        "id": 446092646,
        "sender_full_name": "jthulhu",
        "timestamp": 1718979488
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>how are you stating that a category is empty, just with an equivalence to the empty type?</p>",
        "id": 446093557,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1718979798
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yes</p>",
        "id": 446093602,
        "sender_full_name": "jthulhu",
        "timestamp": 1718979819
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would be happy with a lemma working for an explicit empty type, and letting me precompose the my concrete functor with the equivalence.</p>",
        "id": 446093851,
        "sender_full_name": "jthulhu",
        "timestamp": 1718979891
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I mean... the terminal object is <em>defined</em> as the limit of the empty diagram.</p>",
        "id": 446094017,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1718979944
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so you just need some lemma saying that when <code>C</code> is a category with no objects the <code>C</code> is equivalent to the empty category.</p>",
        "id": 446094123,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1718979972
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"243562\">Adam Topaz</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Limit.20of.20functor.20from.20empty.20category/near/446094017\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I mean... the terminal object is <em>defined</em> as the limit of the empty diagram.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>ah! how silly of me, I didn't even check if that was true by definition</p>",
        "id": 446094194,
        "sender_full_name": "jthulhu",
        "timestamp": 1718980005
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But if you want to use an arbitrary empty category that's not <em>exactly</em> <em>THE</em> empty category, then you will need slightly more work.</p>",
        "id": 446094363,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1718980068
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right... I guess this relatively straightforward, although a bit boilerplaty. Do you know if there happens to already be a lemma in mathlib for this?</p>",
        "id": 446094579,
        "sender_full_name": "jthulhu",
        "timestamp": 1718980140
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here is the equivalence:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib.CategoryTheory.PEmpty</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">open</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CategoryTheory</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Category</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">IsEmpty</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≌</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Discrete</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Empty</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">equivalenceOfIsEmpty</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Discrete</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Empty</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 446094817,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1718980208
    },
